corporate%20clients.%20The%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-is-enneagram-personality-type-number-meaning-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEnneagram%20is%20a%20personality%20model%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20that%20categorizes%20people%20into%20one%20of%20nine%20interconnected%20archetypes%20that%20are%20represented%20by%20numbers%20that%20attempt%20to%20explain%20people's%20characters%20through%20their%20core%20motivations%2C%20desires%2C%20and%20fears.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20ten%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20launched%20my%20firm%20with%20the%20desire%20to%20help%20executives%20become%20better%20leaders%2C%20build%20better%20teams%2C%20and%20build%20better%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20around%20the%20time%20I%20started%20my%20current%20firm%2C%20I%20was%20sitting%20in%20a%20coffee%20shop%20with%20a%20colleague%20and%20she%20told%20me%20about%20this%20thing%20called%20the%20Enneagram.%20I%20thought%20it%20sounded%20silly.%20There's%20no%20science%20behind%20it.%20It's%20all%20based%20on%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20that's%20nice.%20Maybe%20I'll%20look%20into%20it%20someday.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20year%20later%2C%20one%20of%20the%20organizations%20I%20was%20working%20with%20asked%20me%20if%20I%20knew%20about%20the%20Enneagram.%20For%20whatever%20reason%2C%20the%20way%20they%20explained%20it%20landed%20with%20me%20and%20I%20started%20exploring%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20read%20about%20it%20and%20went%20and%20got%20myself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.enneagraminstitute.com%2Ftype-descriptions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etyped%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20an%20Enneagram%20six%20with%20a%20five%20wing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20through%20some%20certification%20and%20formal%20training%20on%20it.%20I%20came%20upon%20an%20Enneagram%20coach%20named%20Beth%20McCord%20and%20started%20reading%20her%20material.%20She%20offered%20a%20certification%20process%20that%20really%20landed%20with%20me.%20I%20got%20licensed%20through%20her%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20I%20got%20interested%20in%20it%2C%20the%20more%20it%20started%20helping%20me%20understand%20myself%20better%20and%20helping%20me%20interact%20with%20the%20people%20around%20me%2C%20primarily%20my%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20mentioned%20it%20to%20one%20of%20my%20largest%20clients%20one%20day%2C%20a%20gentleman%20who%20has%20about%2030%20people%20directly%20underneath%20him.%20I%20asked%20him%20if%20he%20had%20ever%20heard%20of%20the%20Enneagram.%20We%20started%20talking%20about%20it%20and%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20think%20you%20could%20teach%20this%20to%20our%20team%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20very%20confidently%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BSure.%20I%20think%20we%20could%20do%20a%20one-year%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20scurry%20behind%20the%20scenes%20and%20take%20what%20I%20was%20learning%20and%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20coaching%20methodology.%20But%20it%20was%20very%2C%20very%20successful%2C%20such%20that%20they%20decided%20to%20do%20it%20a%20second%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20eventually%20fostered%20it%20into%20becoming%20an%20offering%20in%20my%20firm.%20I've%20rolled%20it%20out%20to%20several%20clients%20since.%20It's%20been%20about%20six%20or%20seven%20years%20that%20we've%20been%20using%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Enneagram%20makes%20up%20about%2025%25%20of%20my%20firm's%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20offer%20two%20workshops%3A%20half%20day%20is%20%244%2C500%20and%20full%20day%20is%20%247%2C500.%20The%20content%20is%20customizable%20based%20on%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it's%20through%20a%20conversation%2C%20workshop%2C%20or%20coaching%20engagement%2C%20we've%20done%20it%20with%20financial%20service%20companies%3B%20we've%20done%20it%20with%20manufacturing%20groups%20and%20technology%20companies.%20I%20have%20one%20client%20who%20is%20a%20food%20manufacturer%20in%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20matter%20what%20they%20do%20or%20how%20they%20operate%20or%20what%20industry%20they're%20in.%20The%20Enneagram%20comes%20up%20when%20two%20primary%20needs%20emerge%20in%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20when%20someone%20is%20really%20seeking%20to%20understand%20themselves%20as%20a%20leader.%20That%20will%20foster%20a%20conversation%20about%20their%20hard%20wiring%20and%20why%20they%20do%20what%20they%20do%20and%20think%20the%20way%20they%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20thread%20of%20conversation%20is%20around%20team%20cohesion.%20The%20Enneagram%20is%20a%20fantastic%20tool%20for%20me%2C%20not%20only%20to%20understand%20myself%2C%20but%20also%20to%20understand%20my%20teammates.%20I%20can%20approach%20them%20in%20a%20different%20way%20when%20I%20understand%20their%20core%20underpinning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224933%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blurred%20photo%20of%20a%20workplace%20meeting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539be2c96f7540cd06620c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223283%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHidalgo%20told%20Insider%20he's%20been%20using%20the%20Enneagram%20in%20his%20workplace%20trainings%20for%20six%20or%20seven%20years.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20give%20our%20clients%20an%20overview%20of%20the%20Enneagram%20to%20start%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20session%20starts%2C%20we%20give%20them%20an%20opportunity%20to%20take%20an%20assessment%20and%20have%20that%20be%20the%20starting%20point%20of%20what%20they%20think%20their%20type%20might%20be.%20We%20walk%20through%20some%20high-level%20understanding%20of%20what%20the%20tool%20is%2C%20how%20it%20works%2C%20and%20how%20you%20can%20use%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20it%20serves%20my%20clients%20to%20come%20in%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20theory%20and%20conceptual%20content.%20So%2C%20after%20that%2C%20we%20practice.%20In%20the%20context%20of%20a%20workshop%2C%20the%20practice%20may%20be%20breaking%20off%20into%20little%20groups.%20We%20create%20a%20scenario%20and%20have%20them%20come%20up%20with%20a%20practical%20way%20they%20can%20apply%20this%20in%20the%20office%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Enneagram%20focuses%20on%20core%20motivations.%20So%2C%20after%20discussing%20core%20motivations%2C%20I%20say%20to%20a%20team%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20you're%20about%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20problem-solving%20or%20conflict-oriented%20conversation%2C%20I%20want%20you%20to%20consider%20the%20person%20you%20are%20talking%20to.%20If%20you%20know%20their%20Enneagram%20type%2C%20think%20about%20the%20core%20motivation%20of%20that%20type%20and%20have%20that%20frame%20how%20you're%20going%20to%20approach%20that%20conversation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20come%20back%20the%20next%20month%20for%20our%20coaching%20meeting%2C%20I%20ask%20them%20for%20a%20story%20of%20how%20that%20changed%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20I%20love%20most%20is%20when%20I%20have%20a%20story%20told%20through%20tears.%20It's%20amazing%20how%20often%20that%20has%20happened.%20People%20will%20come%20back%20and%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20so%20afraid%20to%20talk%20to%20so-and-so%20about%20this%20topic.%20Then%20I%20realized%20where%20they%20were%20coming%20from%20wasn't%20anger%20and%20animosity%20toward%20me.%20They%20were%20coming%20from%20a%20place%20of%20fear.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20ask%20them%20what%20are%20you%20afraid%20of%3F%20And%20it%20broke%20the%20ice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20tell%20these%20conversations%20in%20tears.%20I%20didn't%20realize%20I%20could%20connect%20with%20people%20at%20that%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20see%20some%20patterns%20in%20my%20Enneagram%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETypes%20threes%2C%20sevens%2C%20and%20eights%20tend%20to%20be%20your%20leaders.%20They%20lead%20in%20different%20styles%20and%20for%20different%20types%20of%20reasons%2C%20but%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20your%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20trend%20I%20see%20is%20that%20out%20of%20the%20nine%20types%2C%20the%20most%20infrequent%20type%20you'll%20see%20in%20a%20leadership%20position%20will%20be%20a%20four.%20Type%20fours%20tend%20to%20be%20very%20internal%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20thinking%20and%20processing.%20They're%20very%20comfortable%20being%20on%20the%20fringes%20and%20on%20the%20outside%20looking%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20see%20that%20types%20one%2C%20five%2C%20and%20six%20tend%20to%20be%20very%20driven%20toward%20process.%20They%20stick%20to%20the%20script.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224833%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20diagram%20of%20the%20nine%20Enneagram%20types%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539bec496f7540cd06620f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223522%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Enneagram%20is%20a%20personality%20model%20that%20categorizes%20people%20into%20one%20of%20nine%20interconnected%20archetypes%20that%20are%20represented%20by%20numbers%20that%20attempt%20to%20explain%20people's%20characters%20through%20their%20core%20motivations%2C%20desires%2C%20and%20fears.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvery%20once%20in%20a%20while%20you%20have%20a%20skeptical%20executive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20don't%20really%20try%20to%20combat%20anybody%20who%20doesn't%20want%20to%20bring%20the%20Enneagram%20in.%20When%20I%20start%20describing%20the%20Enneagram%2C%20it%20just%20somehow%20lands%20because%20it's%20not%20typical%20corporate%20speak.%20It's%20different.%20And%20people%20seem%20to%20want%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20finding%20more%20and%20more%20that%20there%20is%20a%20very%20low%20tolerance%20for%20anything%20that's%20not%20authentic.%20The%20Enneagram%20requires%20each%20of%20us%20to%20look%20inside%20to%20deal%20with%20things%20like%20core%20motivations%2C%20childhood%20messages%2C%20things%20we%20want%20to%20hear%2C%20and%20core%20longings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20reward%20I%20get%20is%20when%20these%20conversations%20move%20from%20their%20workplace%20into%20their%20personal%20lives.%20I'm%20amazed%20at%20how%20many%20people%20come%20back%20and%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20use%20this%20at%20the%20office%2C%20but%20I%20did%20use%20it%20at%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20to%20see%20that%20there%20is%20a%20significant%20change%20and%20transition%20in%20how%20they're%20interacting%20with%20family%20and%20those%20closest%20to%20them.%20If%20they%20can%20change%20their%20lives%20and%20change%20things%20at%20home%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20make%20them%20a%20better%20employee%20and%20a%20better%20staff%20member%20and%20a%20better%20team%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeminars%20are%20great%2C%20books%20are%20great%2C%20conferences%20are%20great.%20But%20there's%20something%20about%20learning%20about%20myself%20together%20in%20a%20community%20that%20brings%20people%20together.%20And%20the%20Enneagram%20is%20a%20great%2C%20great%20tool%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-coach-uses-enneagram-corporate-trainings-workshop-personality-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698351698000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539bcb396f7540cd0662080%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-coach-uses-enneagram-corporate-trainings-workshop-personality-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jay%20Hidalgo%20is%20a%20leadership%20coach%20who%20uses%20the%20Enneagram%20model%20in%20corporate%20workshops.%20He%20told%20Insider%20the%20tool%20is%20great%20for%20building%20team%20cohesion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Erin%20