0Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20a%C2%A0Houston%20bankruptcy%20attorney.%20She%20represented%20another%20Corizon%20successor%20company%2C%20YesCare%2C%20in%20the%20negotiations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesCare%20got%20all%20of%20Corizon's%20corrections%20contracts%20after%20the%20company%20engaged%20in%20a%20controversial%20legal%20maneuver%20last%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Ecalled%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20involved%20splitting%20Corizon%20in%20two.%20The%20other%20company%2C%20Tehum%2C%20was%20saddled%20with%20most%20of%20Corizon's%20liabilities%20and%2C%20in%20February%2C%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221464%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20letter%20from%20the%20US%20Senate%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653aa502356802a56be500ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221019%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENine%20US%20senators%20have%20written%20to%20Corizon%20successor%20companies%20Tehum%20Care%20Services%20and%20YesCare%20demanding%20answers%20about%20Corizon's%20efforts%20to%20%26quot%3Bmanipulate%20bankruptcy%20law.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EUS%20Senate%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20has%20been%20following%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Ethe%20story%20of%20Corizon%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20August%2C%20revealing%20in%20an%20investigation%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20leaked%20documents%2C%20business%20filings%2C%20public-records%20requests%2C%20voluminous%20court%20filings%2C%20and%20dozens%20of%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20that%20a%20group%20of%20investors%20with%20dubious%20business%20histories%20quietly%20bought%20out%20the%20company%20in%202021%20and%20engaged%20in%20financial%20maneuvers%20so%20opaque%20and%20controversial%20that%20a%20former%20Corizon%20CEO%20described%20