He%20goes%20on%20to%20say%20that%20the%20relationship%20%26quot%3Braises%20reasonable%20doubts%20as%20to%20the%20fairness%20of%20the%20mediation%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20from%20nine%20US%20senators%2C%20including%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20Cory%20Booker%2C%20and%20the%20Judiciary%20Committee's%20chair%2C%20Dick%20Durbin%2C%20raises%20the%20issue%20as%20well.%20%26quot%3BCorizon's%20tactics%20are%20further%20called%20into%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20write%2C%20%26quot%3Bgiven%20the%20secret%20romantic%20relationship%20between%20the%20judge%20mediating%20the%20plan%20negotiations%20and%20the%20attorney%20representing%20YesCare%20in%20the%20negotiations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20ruling%20by%20Lopez%20on%20objections%20from%20creditors%20could%20come%20as%20soon%20as%20early%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Extremely%20low%20payouts%20for%20prisoners%20and%20their%20families.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bankruptcy%20plan%20breaks%20creditors%20down%20into%20several%20classes.%20The%20largest%20is%20the%20medical-malpractice%20claimants%2C%20who%20collectively%20say%20they're%20owed%20almost%20%241.1%20billion.%20Claims%20by%20a%20class%20composed%20of%20vendors%20such%20as%20hospitals%20amount%20to%20far%20less%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%24111%20million.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20proposed%20%2437%20million%20settlement%20gives%20the%20malpractice%20claimants%20only%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20total.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20%26quot%3Btwo%20classes%20of%20unsecured%20claimants%20get%20wildly%20different%20shares%20of%20the%20settlement%20funds%2C%26quot%3B%20Kevin%20Eckhardt%2C%20the%20deputy%20managing%20editor%20for%20legal%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freorg.com%2Famericas-court-opinion-review%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReorg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20restructuring%20and%20credit-focused%20research%20firm%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20this%20month.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHector%20Garcia%20Jr.%2C%20whose%20father%2C%20Hector%20Garcia%2C%20died%20after%20three%20days%20in%20Corizon's%20care%20at%20a%20New%20Mexico%20jail%2C%20previously%20described%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprominent-bankruptcy-judge-recused-under-investigation-after-undisclosed-romantic-relationship-exposed-2023-10%5C%22%3E%245%2C000%20allocated%20to%20each%20claimant%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20slap%20in%20the%20face.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20amount%20wouldn't%20even%20cover%20what%20the%20family%20had%20already%20spent%20since%20his%20father's%20death%2C%20including%20more%20than%20%242%2C500%20for%20funeral%20services%20and%20%245%2C000%20to%20retain%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20you%20come%20up%20with%20an%20amount%20like%20that%20%E2%80%94%20%245%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20just%20to%20say%2C%20'Here's%20for%20the%20death%20of%20your%20brother'%3F%26quot%3B%20asked%20Belen%20Lowery%2C%20the%20elder%20Garcia's%20sister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators'%20letter%20urges%20YesCare%20CEO%20Jeff%20Sholey%20and%20Tehum%20director%20Isaac%20Lefkowitz%20%26quot%3Bto%20use%20the%20full%20financial%20capabilities%20of%20YesCare%2C%20Tehum%2C%20and%20any%20other%20entities%20as%20appropriate%2C%20to%20provide%20full%20relief%20for%20meritorious%20claims%20against%20Corizon%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20by%20incarcerated%20people%20and%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Numerous%20liability%20releases%20without%20'basic%20information%20about%20who%20these%20individuals%20are.'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20its%20numerous%20objections%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee%20called%20out%20the%20lack%20of%20legal%20justification%20for%20broad%20releases%20the%20plan%20proposes%20for%20a%20number%20of%20individuals%20connected%20with%20Corizon%20and%20YesCare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20objection%20specifically%20mentions%20Lefkowitz%2C%20who%20has%20served%20as%20a%20director%20of%20Corizon%2C%20Tehum%2C%20and%20YesCare%3B%20Sara%20Tirschwell%2C%20Corizon%20and%20YesCare's%20former%20CEO%3B%20Sholey%2C%20YesCare's%20current%20CEO%3B%20YesCare's%20chief%20legal%20officer%2C%20Jeffrey%20Scott%20King%3B%20its%20chief%20medical%20officer%2C%20Ayodeji%20Olawale%20Ladele%3B%20a%20YesCare%20finance%20executive%2C%20Michelle%20Rice%3B%20and%20Jennifer%20Finger%2C%20whose%20social-media%20profiles%20say%20she%20has%20served%20as%20counsel%20for%20both%20Corizon%20and%20YesCare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETehum's%20disclosure%20statement%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20contain%20basic%20information%20about%20who%20these%20individuals%20are%20or%20their%20connection%20to%20the%20Debtor%20and%20other%20entities%20involved%20in%20the%20combination%20and%20divisional%20mergers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20objection%20says%2C%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20Two-Step.%20Nor%20does%20the%20disclosure%20say%20%26quot%3Bwhether%20these%20individuals%20are%20contributing%20to%20the%20settlement%20in%20return%20for%20the%20releases%20of%20non-debtors%2C%20and%20if%20so%2C%20how%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreditors%20have%20filed%20objections%20to%20these%20liability%20releases%2C%20with%20the%20Arizona%20Department%20of%20Corrections%2C%20Rehabilitation%2C%20and%20Reentry%20saying%20that%20before%20supporting%20the%20bankruptcy%20plan%2C%20it%20would%20need%20to%20see%20a%20list%20of%20who%20contributed%20financially%20to%20the%20settlement%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20they%20paid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators'%20letter%20requests%20that%20Sholey%20and%20Lefkowitz%20produce%20a%20full%20description%20of%20YesCare's%20and%20Tehum's%20leadership%20structures%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20leadership%20and%20ownership%20of%20all%20parent%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Large%20payments%20to%20insider%20companies.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Insider%20reported%20on%20financial%20records%20showing%20that%20at%20least%20%2448%20million%20had%20been%20transferred%20from%20Corizon%20or%20Tehum%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Ewhat%20Tehum%20called%20%26quot%3Baffiliates%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0or%20companies%20controlled%20by%20insiders%2C%20from%20December%202021%20to%20November%202022.%20Some%20of%20those%20payments%2C%20Tehum%20noted%2C%20were%20offset%20by%20incoming%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20subsequent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230929000000000002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisclosure%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20case%20confirms%20that%20at%20least%20%2430%20million%20was%20sent%20from%20company%20coffers%20to%20companies%20controlled%20by%20insiders%20%E2%80%94%20funds%20that%20could%20potentially%20have%20been%20used%20to%20bolster%20payouts%20in%20the%20settlement.%20Just%20before%20splitting%20the%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3ECorizon's%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20moved%20millions%20of%20dollars%20into%20new%20bank%20accounts%20with%20a%20curious%20feature%3A%20The%20company's%20chief%20financial%20officer%20couldn't%20view%20the%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20bookkeepers%20were%20most%20likely%20unaware%20when%2C%20from%20December%202021%20to%20November%202022%2C%20%2424.5%20million%20was%20moved%20out%20of%20those%20accounts%20and%20into%20the%20account%20of%20M2%20LoanCo%2C%20a%20lender%20with%20ties%20to%20Tehum%2C%20according%20to%20the%20disclosure.%20(The%20disclosure%20notes%20that%20M2%20has%20disputed%20this%20amount.)%20Lefkowitz%20is%20a%20director%20of%20both%20M2%20and%20Tehum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Corizon%20paid%20%245.5%20million%20from%20December%202021%20to%20May%202022%20to%20Geneva%20Consulting%20LLC%2C%20according%20to%20the%20disclosure%20statement.%20Lefkowitz%20had%20a%20controlling%20interest%20in%20Geneva%2C%20according%20to%20a%20motion%20submitted%20in%20a%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20Tehum%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri%20Health%20Care%20system%20and%20a%20local%20hospital.%20Geneva%20also%20manages%20and%20financially%20supports%20YesCare%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911031-yescares-alabama-department-of-corrections-program-proposal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebid%20for%20a%20state%20prison%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%20obtained%20by%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators'%20letter%20raises%20concerns%20about%20a%20range%20of%20company%20tactics%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3Bquestionable%20and%20unjust%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20%26quot%3Bdiverting%20millions%20of%20Corizon%20dollars%20to%20other%20companies%20that%20the%20investors%20personally%20owned%20or%20were%20associated%20with%2C%20likely%20limiting%20funds%20available%20for%20victims.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20June%20motion%2C%20several%20creditors%20said%20the%20transactions%20could%20be%20tantamount%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfraudulent%20transfer%26quot%3B%20of%20assets%20outside%20their%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20federal%20bankruptcy%20code%2C%20a%20fraudulent-transfer%20claim%20requires%20a%20showing%20of%20intent%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bto%20hinder%2C%20delay%2C%20or%20defraud%26quot%3B%20creditors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20showing%20intent%2C%20Edward%20Janger%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20Brooklyn%20Law%20School%2C%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uniformlaws.org%2Fcommittees%2Fcommunity-home%3FCommunityKey%3D64ee1ccc-a3ae-4a5e-a18f-a5ba8206bf49%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniform%20Voidable%20Transactions%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20adopted%20in%20some%20form%20by%20most%20states%2C%20provides%20a%20list%20of%20factors%20to%20consider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIntent%20can%20be%20established%20by%20looking%20at%20the%20objective%20characteristics%20of%20the%20transaction%2C%26quot%3B%20Janger%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20need%20a%20smoking%20gun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20the%20factors%20may%20be%20present%20in%20Tehum's%20case%2C%20including%20a%20pattern%20of%20transfers%20to%20insiders%2C%20the%20concealment%20of%20transfers%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20company%20became%20insolvent%20shortly%20after%20the%20insider%20transfers%20were%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20'Dishonest'%20testimony%20by%20a%20Tehum%20director.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELefkowitz%2C%20Tehum's%20director%2C%20is%20a%20pivotal%20figure%20in%20the%20bankruptcy.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20the%20investors%20who%20bought%20Corizon%20and%20took%20it%20into%20the%20Two-Step.%20And%20he's%20served%20as%20one%20of%20Tehum's%20representatives%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators'%20letter%20accuses%20principals%20of%20the%20company%20of%20%26quot%3Bstonewalling%20during%20meetings%20with%20creditors%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20August%20motion%20by%20creditors%20went%20further%2C%20arguing%20that%20Lefkowitz%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20dishonest%20throughout%20this%20case%26quot%3B%20about%20Tehum's%20affiliations%20with%20Geneva.%20Dishonesty%20during%20a%20bankruptcy%20proceeding%20is%20an%20infraction%20severe%20enough%20under%20federal%20bankruptcy%20code%20to%20be%20grounds%20for%20handing%20control%20to%20an%20independent%20trustee%20if%20committed%20by%20%26quot%3Bcurrent%20management.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELefkowitz%20repeatedly%20said%20under%20oath%20during%20a%20June%20creditor%20call%20that%20he%20didn't%20know%20who%20owned%20Geneva%20Consulting%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20Corizon%20paid%20%245.5%20million.%20Yet%20in%20a%20February%202022%20email%20to%20Corizon's%20top%20executives%2C%20introduced%20as%20an%20exhibit%20in%20court%2C%20Lefkowitz%20said%20Geneva%20was%20a%20wholly%20owned%20subsidiary%20of%20Genesis%20Healthcare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreditors%20seized%20on%20what%20they%20called%20his%20%26quot%3Bdishonest%26quot%3B%20testimony%20in%20arguing%20at%20a%20September%20hearing%20that%20the%20company%20should%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20a%20trustee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELopez%20denied%20the%20motion%2C%20arguing%20that%20as%20a%20director%20Lefkowitz%20did%20not%20meet%20the%20bankruptcy%20code's%20definition%20of%20current%20management.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%20Trustee%20is%20supposed%20to%20watchdog%20bankruptcy%20crimes%2C%20criminal%20referrals%20are%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202022%20fiscal%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Justice%20Department%20data%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee%20made%20just%202%2C104%20bankruptcy-related%20criminal%20referrals.%20By%20comparison%2C%20there%20were%20almost%20388%2C000%20bankruptcy%20filings%20in%20the%202022%20calendar%20year.%20Of%20those%20referrals%2C%20only%20seven%20%E2%80%94%200.3%25%20of%20all%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20had%20led%20to%20formal%20charges%20as%20of%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Trustee%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20whether%20it%20was%20considering%20a%20criminal%20referral%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Failure%20to%20disclose%20a%20data%20breach.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20September%2C%20Tehum's%20chief%20restructuring%20officer%2C%20Russell%20Perry%2C%20admitted%20during%20a%20hearing%20that%20the%20company%20had%20been%20party%20to%20a%20cyber%20incident.%20He%20did%20not%20provide%20further%20details.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20objection%20filed%20by%20the%20US%20Trustee%20says%20Tehum%20provided%20some%20details%20months%20earlier%20%E2%80%94%20at%20a%20March%2020%20hearing%20attended%20only%20by%20Tehum's%20representatives%2C%20representatives%20of%20the%20major%20creditors%2C%20and%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20US%20Trustee.%20There%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee's%20representative%20told%20the%20company%20it%20was%20required%20to%20disclose%20the%20incident%20to%20creditors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETehum%20later%20sought%20court%20approval%20to%20hire%20Baker%20%26amp%3B%20Hostetler%20LLP%2C%20a%20national%20law%20firm%2C%20to%20handle%20cyber-related%20issues.%20Tehum%20said%20Baker%20would%20provide%20%26quot%3Bincident%20investigation%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdata%20recovery%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20help%20%26quot%3Bpreparing%2C%20mailing%2C%20and%20submitting%20all%20required%20individual%20and%20regulatory%20notifications.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee's%20objection%20says%2C%20though%20Tehum%20spent%20funds%20to%20retain%20this%20firm%2C%20%26quot%3Bto%20date%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20disclosure%20to%20the%20public%20and%20creditors%20regarding%20the%20incident.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaker%20%26amp%3B%20Hostetler%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Trustee%20didn't%20initially%20believe%20any%20patient%20records%20were%20at%20risk.%20But%20then%2C%20as%20Insider%20reported%2C%20Lefkowitz%20said%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23919674-continued-section-341-meeting-of-creditors%23document%2Fp40%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeposition%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20some%20Tehum%20records%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20including%20sensitive%20prisoner%20health%20files%20%E2%80%94%20had%20been%20stored%20on%20his%20email%20or%20in%20a%20Dropbox%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221558%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20from%20a%20deposition%20from%20a%20Mr.%20Lefkowitz%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65397a6a0487ff031cae9d1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22735%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20May%202023%2C%20Isaac%20Lefkowitz%2C%20Tehum's%20sole%20director%2C%20said%20under%20oath%20that%20the%20company's%20electronic%20records%20were%20%26quot%3Bstored%20on%20my%20email%2C%20on%20my%20Dropbox%26quot%3B%20accounts.%3Cp%3EUS%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20never%20explained%20in%20open%20court%20what%20precipitated%20the%20hire%20of%20Baker%20%26amp%3B%20Hostetler.%20But%20an%20objection%20submitted%20by%20a%20creditor's%20attorneys%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20Insider%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24085039-adree-edmos-objection-to-debtors-emergency-motion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobtained%20an%20unredacted%20copy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20says%20Corizon%20was%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20ransomware%20attack.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FFalconFeedsio%2Fstatus%2F1642769196269412354%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20cybersecurity%20firm%20and%20an%20alert%20from%20the%20information-security%20site%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redpacketsecurity.com%2Froyal-ransomware-victim-corizon-healthcare%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERedPacket%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20suggest%20as%20much.%20Both%20cite%20a%20post%20from%20the%20dark%20web%20claiming%20the%20breached%20documents%20included%20legal%20and%20health%20records%20pertaining%20to%20the%20company's%20incarcerated%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20unclear%20when%20the%20Debtor%20became%20aware%20of%20the%20theft%20%E2%80%94%20or%20whether%20they%20have%20reported%20the%20incident%20to%20the%20FBI%20and%20CISA%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20creditors'%20attorneys%20wrote%20in%20their%20April%20filing%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Cybersecurity%20and%20Infrastructure%20Security%20Agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20regulations%20require%20a%20breach%20notification%20in%20most%20cases.%20Representatives%20for%20CISA%20and%20the%20FBI%20declined%20to%20comment%3B%20HHS%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Alabama%20prisoner%2C%20Tracey%20Grissom%2C%20filed%20suit%20against%20Corizon%20claiming%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20her%20own%20feces%20for%20months%20because%20Corizon%20providers%20failed%20to%20give%20her%20a%20properly%20fitted%20ostomy%20bag.%20Her%20attorney%20raised%20the%20data%20breach%20in%20an%20objection%20filed%20last%20week%2C%20saying%20Grissom%20had%20not%20been%20notified%20about%20the%20potential%20theft%20of%20her%20sensitive%20data%2C%20as%20required%20by%20HIPAA%2C%20the%20medical%20privacy%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221583%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20white%20building%20labeled%20Julia%20Tutwiler%20Prison%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653aa62a96f7540cd066d33c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221187%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJulia%20Tutwiler%20Prison%20for%20Women%20in%20Wetumpka%2C%20Alabama%2C%20where%20Tracey%20Grissom%20alleges%20she%20suffered%20medical%20neglect%20under%20Corizon's%20care.%3Cp%3ERivers%20A.%20Langley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%26quot%3BThe%20data%20breach%20constitutes%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20privacy%20of%20each%20patient%20treated%20by%20the%20debtors%2C%20which%20may%20number%20into%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20objection%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20HIPAA%20violations%20may%20result%20in%20civil%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20criminal%20%E2%80%94%20penalties.%3Cp%3ERoman%20Sannikov%2C%20a%20cyberthreat%20intelligence%20researcher%20who%20founded%20Constellation%20Cyber%20LLC%2C%20said%20the%20available%20evidence%20suggested%20that%20Corizon%20might%20have%20paid%20a%20ransom%20to%20keep%20patients'%20personal%20information%20off%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESannikov%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Btypically%20means%20that%20the%20company%20has%20paid%20a%20ransom%26quot%3B%20when%20a%20data%20breach%20appears%20on%20an%20alert%20website%2C%20the%20data%20is%20not%20leaked%2C%20and%20yet%20the%20company's%20name%20is%20removed%20from%20the%20site%2C%20as%20appears%20to%20have%20happened%20in%20this%20case.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20the%20FBI%20and%20CISA%20sent%20out%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisa.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fcybersecurity-advisories%2Faa23-061a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoint%20alert%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20same%20ransomware%20group%20that%20appears%20to%20have%20targeted%20Corizon%2C%20saying%20it%20had%20recently%20made%20%26quot%3Bransom%20demands%20ranging%20from%20approximately%20%241%20million%20to%20%2411%20million%26quot%3B%20in%20bitcoin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20hasn't%20yet%20sought%20approval%20from%20Lopez%20in%20court%20to%20make%20such%20a%20payment.%20And%20the%20US%20Trustee%2C%20in%20its%20objection%2C%20said%20Tehum%20hadn't%20told%20creditors%20whether%20voting%20for%20the%20settlement%20would%20release%20the%20company%20and%20other%20parties%20from%20liability%20for%20any%20claims%20related%20to%20the%20information%20breach.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disclosure%20statement%20%26quot%3Bmust%20be%20modified%20to%20include%20information%20concerning%20the%20data%20incident%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20incident%20on%20potential%20claims%20and%20the%20effect%20of%20the%20third-party%20releases%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20objection%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20settlement%20isn't%20a%20done%20deal%20yet.%20Lopez%20raised%20so%20many%20concerns%20at%20the%20October%2017%20hearing%20that%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fundamental%20deal%20has%20to%20be%20reconsidered.%26quot%3B%20Once%20it's%20finalized%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20creditors%20still%20have%20to%20approve%20it%20in%20a%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20involvement%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fust%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20US%20Trustee's%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20huge%20development.%20The%20job%20of%20that%20office%2C%20the%20agency%20says%2C%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bpromote%20the%20integrity%20and%20efficiency%20of%20the%20bankruptcy%20system%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20all%20stakeholders.%26quot%3B%20Historically%2C%20the%20office%20says%2C%20it%20has%20played%20a%20critical%20role%20in%20policing%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20and%20has%20taken%20%26quot%3Ba%20narrow%20view%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20authority%20of%20bankruptcy%20courts%20to%20release%20third%20parties%20from%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20filed%20objections%2C%20motions%2C%20or%20complaints%20to%20disclosure%20statements%20in%20only%20249%20cases%20in%20the%202021%20fiscal%20year%2C%20the%20period%20covered%20by%20its%20latest%20annual%20report%3B%20the%20report%20says%2098%25%20of%20those%20interventions%20were%20successful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20nine%20senators%20who%20authored%20the%20letter%20have%20given%20YesCare%20and%20Tehum%20until%20November%208%20to%20answer%20their%20detailed%20inquiries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-deal-settlement-threatened-issues-objections-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698349898000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539792d96f7540cd065ee90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-deal-settlement-threatened-issu