d%20and%20two%20babies%2C%20Maria%20and%20Ascia%2C%20and%20her%20in-laws.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20later%2C%20Fatin%20heard%20from%20neighbors%20that%20her%20house%20had%20been%20completely%20demolished%20in%20an%20aerial%20strike.%20When%20her%20husband%20returned%20to%20see%20if%20anything%20could%20be%20salvaged%20from%20the%20rubble%2C%20it%20was%20heartbreaking%20for%20him%20to%20see%20the%20girls'%20dolls%20and%20clothes%20thrown%20in%20the%20street.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Istanbul%2C%20Abdullah%20and%20I%20watched%20on%20Al%20Jazeera%20as%20places%20with%20cherished%20memories%20in%20Gaza%20City%20were%20destroyed%20live%20on%20air.%20We%20watched%20as%20dozens%20of%20buildings%20were%20flattened%20to%20the%20ground%20in%20Al-Remal%2C%20Abdullah's%20old%20neighborhood.%20Abdullah's%20family%20house%20was%20one%20of%20them%2C%20but%20thankfully%2C%20just%20hours%20earlier%2C%20his%20parents%20had%20evacuated%20to%20the%20home%20of%20Abdullah's%20brother%20in%20the%20Tal%20Al-Hawa%20neighborhood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20watched%20these%20beautiful%20houses%20fall%2C%20I%20asked%20myself%20how%20demolishing%20entire%20neighborhoods%20can%20be%20a%20punishment%20for%20Hamas%3F%20I%20still%20don't%20know%20the%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20takes%20shelter%20under%20a%20staircase.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a9c9296f7540cd066bc60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22699%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPhoto%20for%20my%20sister%20Yasmeen%20while%20taking%20shelter%20under%20the%20stairs%20of%20her%20building%20because%20it's%20said%20it's%20a%20safe%20area%20to%20hide%20in.%3Cp%3EMuhammad%20Ghanem%20(used%20with%20permission)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3ESupplies%20of%20fuel%2C%20electricity%2C%20and%20water%20had%20stopped%20coming%20into%20Gaza.%20Soon%2C%20Gaza's%20main%20power%20plant%20switched%20off.%20In%20Gaza%20City%2C%20you%20could%20hope%20for%20an%20hour%20of%20power%20a%20day%20to%20get%20WiFi%20and%20to%20charge%20the%20power%20banks%20for%20cell%20phones.%20My%20relatives%20kept%20their%20phones%20on%20at%20different%20times%2C%20so%20to%20reach%20one%20I'd%20have%20to%20call%20multiple%20numbers.%C2%A0%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20live%20in%20a%20five-story%20building%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Gaza%20City%20that%20my%20father%20had%20built%2040%20years%20ago.%20My%20four%20brothers%20%E2%80%94%20Hussam%2C%20Hazem%2C%20Alaa%2C%20and%20Hatem%20%E2%80%94%20live%20there%20too%2C%20along%20with%20their%20families%2C%20all%20in%20separate%20apartments.%20Soon%2C%20my%20aunt%20arrived%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20her%20son's%20family%2C%20after%20fleeing%20their%20home%20near%20Gaza's%20eastern%20border.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocated%20in%20a%20residential%20neighborhood%20with%20no%20government%20buildings%20or%20obvious%20targets%20nearby%2C%20it%20has%20always%20felt%20relatively%20safe.%20When%20I%20lived%20there%20as%20a%20child%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20windows%2C%20but%20to%20keep%20them%20open%2C%20during%20bombardments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20after%20the%20war%20started%2C%20I%20was%20on%20Facebook%20searching%20for%20news%20and%20saw%20something%20that%20made%20me%20let%20out%20a%20gasp%3A%20A%20spokesman%20for%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%20had%20posted%20a%20map%20of%20our%20neighborhood%20with%20a%20message%20telling%20people%20to%20evacuate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20reached%20my%20brother%2C%20Hazem%2C%20he%20said%20they%20hadn't%20heard%20about%20the%20evacuation%20order.%20But%20he%20said%20they%20could%20hear%20constant%20explosions%20and%20he%20thought%20it%20was%20very%20risky%20to%20move%20outside.%20Home%20still%20felt%20like%20the%20safest%20option.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20said%20goodbye%2C%20but%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20I%20could%20not%20leave%20my%20phone.%20Sick%20with%20worry%2C%20I%20scanned%20Telegram%20for%20updates%20from%20the%20ground.%20My%20family%20stayed%20where%20they%20were%20and%20each%20message%20from%20them%20brought%20fresh%20relief%20that%20they%20were%20still%20alive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvacuate%20the%20north%2C%20but%20to%20where%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20Friday%20morning%2C%20Oct.%2013%2C%20I%20woke%20up%20to%20a%20missed%20call%20from%20Yazmina%2C%20my%20friend%20in%20Istanbul.%20Abdullah%20and%20I%20were%20never%20the%20type%20of%20people%20who%20took%20our%20phones%20with%20us%20to%20bed.%20That%20had%20changed%2C%20and%20for%20days%20we'd%20been%20reaching%20for%20our%20phones%20the%20minute%20we%20opened%20our%20eyes%20in%20the%20morning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20called%20Yazmina%20back.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20Israel%20had%20announced%20that%201%20million%20civilians%20in%20northern%20Gaza%2C%20including%20Gaza%20City%2C%20should%20evacuate%20within%2024%20hours.%20To%20where%2C%20it%20wasn't%20clear.%20Scores%20of%20people%2C%20including%20most%20of%20Yazmina's%20family%2C%20were%20already%20heading%20south.%20People%20were%20taking%20refuge%20in%20the%20homes%20of%20people%20they%20barely%20knew.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20called%20my%20parents'%20home%20and%20I%20asked%20my%20dad%20what%20he%20thought.%20My%20dad%20is%20a%20great%20father%20%E2%80%94%20more%20interested%20in%20music%20than%20politics.%20Knowing%20how%20attached%20he%20is%20to%20the%20building%20he'd%20lived%20in%20for%20decades%2C%20I%20expected%20his%20answer.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20repeating%20the%201948%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20year%20Palestinians%20were%20removed%20from%20our%20land%20and%20Israel%20declared%20itself%20an%20independent%20state.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20leaving%20my%20house%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20I'll%20be%20killed.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20oldest%20brother%20wanted%20to%20go.%20But%20the%20three%20younger%20brothers%20preferred%20to%20stay%20put%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20we%20don't%20have%20relatives%20in%20the%20south.%20We%20were%20all%20also%20worried%20about%20my%20mother.%20She%20is%20paralyzed%20and%20rarely%20leaves%20the%20house%2C%20except%20for%20the%20occasional%20trip%20to%20the%20beach%20in%20her%20wheelchair.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20them%20I%20would%20call%20every%20two%20hours%20to%20get%20them%20news%20and%20to%20know%20their%20plans.%20Beyond%20what%20they%20could%20hear%20and%20see%20from%20their%20windows%2C%20I%20was%20my%20family's%20link%20to%20news%20and%20information.%20I%20could%20see%20on%20Instagram%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20people%20were%20already%20starting%20to%20pour%20out%20of%20Gaza%20City%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20north.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20not%20to%20push%20them%20one%20way%20or%20another%2C%20since%20I%20knew%20I%20would%20be%20living%20with%20a%20forever%20guilt%20if%20by%20chance%20they%20took%20my%20recommendation%20and%20were%20all%20killed.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20of%20these%20calls%2C%20they%20said%20a%20friend%20of%20Hazam's%20had%20offered%20to%20host%20them.%20So%20it%20was%20agreed%3A%20All%2035%20of%20them%20would%20leave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20niece%2C%20Ne'ama%2C%2021%2C%20sent%20me%20photos%20of%20the%20family%20packing%20and%20her%20own%20crying%20face.%20They%20gathered%20their%20birth%20certificates%2C%20education%20certificates%2C%20and%20other%20documents%20they'd%20need%20to%20restart%20their%20lives%20if%20the%20house%20was%20hit.%20They%20packed%20blankets%2C%20cooking%20gas%2C%20and%20cash.%20They%20would%20make%20two%20separate%20trips%20in%20my%20father's%20two%20vehicles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20takes%20a%20selfie%20while%20holding%20a%20baby.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a9d38356802a56be4efc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22622%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20selfie%20taken%20by%20Ne'ama%20shows%20her%20holding%20her%20little%20sister%20Farah%20minutes%20before%20evacuating%20from%20our%20family%20home%20in%20Gaza%20City.%3Cp%3ENe'ama%20Ayyoub%20(used%20with%20permission)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20my%20father%20had%20said%2C%20the%20scenes%20of%20leaving%20their%20homes%20with%20mattresses%20tied%20to%20the%20tops%20of%20their%20cars%20felt%20like%20a%20replay%20of%201948.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20judgment%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Ne'ama%20wrote%20to%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drive%20to%20the%20south%20of%20Gaza%20usually%20takes%20about%2015%20minutes.%20Now%2C%20two%20hours.%20Elsewhere%2C%20we%20heard%20that%20taxi%20drivers%20were%20demanding%20%24100%20for%20the%20journey%2C%20up%20from%20the%20usual%20%2410.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20agreed%20that%20two%20of%20my%20sisters%2C%20Hanadi%20and%20Yasmeen%2C%20would%20also%20flee%20to%20the%20south%20with%20their%20families%20and%20in-laws%2C%20and%20take%20shelter%20at%20the%20same%20home%20as%20my%20parents%20and%20brothers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYasmeen%20spent%20most%20of%20the%20day%20searching%20for%20a%20car%20before%20finally%20finding%20some%20seats%20with%20her%20sister-in-law.%20Three%20months%20ago%2C%20Yasmeen%20lost%20her%20only%20child%2C%20Sophia.%20She%20had%20been%20born%20prematurely%2C%20with%20underdeveloped%20lungs%20and%20a%20heart%20defect%2C%20and%20had%20been%20hooked%20up%20to%20an%20oxygen%20machine%20to%20breathe.%20She%20lived%20for%20just%20nine%20months.%20On%20the%20day%20of%20the%20evacuation%2C%20Yasmeen%20told%20me%20she%20was%20relieved%20that%20Sophia%20was%20at%20peace%2C%20that%20she%20wasn't%20sure%20Sophia%20would%20have%20survived%20this%20ordeal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20my%20other%20sisters%2C%20Siham%20and%20Taghreed%2C%20decided%20to%20stay%20with%20their%20children%20in%20Gaza%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiham%2C%20who%20lives%20near%20the%20seaport%20where%20naval%20artillery%20is%20often%20fired%2C%20said%20she's%20very%20afraid%2C%20but%20that%20if%20she%20is%20going%20to%20be%20killed%20she%20prefers%20to%20be%20in%20her%20own%20home%20%E2%80%94%20not%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20a%20stranger%20%E2%80%94%20when%20it%20happens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20place%20to%20sleep%2C%20water%20to%20drink%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20got%20to%20the%20home%20of%20Hazem's%20friend%2C%20they%20were%20surprised%20to%20find%20more%20than%20100%20people%20taking%20shelter%20there%20already.%C2%A0The%20rooms%20were%20packed%2C%20and%20there%20were%20long%20lines%20to%20use%20the%20toilet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister-in-law%20had%20to%20haggle%20so%20that%20my%20mother%20could%20sleep%20on%20a%20couch%20rather%20than%20on%20the%20floor.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20humiliating%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Ne'ama%20told%20me%2C%20crying.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20stand%20seeing%20my%20grandmother%20sleeping%20on%20a%20sofa.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20did%20have%20water%2C%20though%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20well%20the%20family%20used%20for%20agriculture.%20The%20family%20had%20been%20trading%20some%20of%20that%20water%20for%20bread%2C%20which%20was%20in%20short%20supply%2C%20so%20everyone%20could%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20selfie%20shows%20a%20large%20family%20relaxing%20near%20a%20parked%20car.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a9a1d96f7540cd066b6df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20selfie%20taken%20by%20my%20nephew%20Hammoud%20that%20shows%20the%20family%20spending%20an%20afternoon%20outdoors%20while%20they%20take%20refuge%20in%20the%20south%20of%20Gaza.%20My%20mother%20is%20seen%2C%20at%20center%2C%20and%20my%20father%20is%20to%20the%20right.%3Cp%3EHammoud%20Ayyoub%20(used%20with%20permission)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20nephew%2C%20Hammoud%2C%20told%20me%20he'd%20managed%20to%20take%20a%20cold%20shower%2C%20I%20asked%20if%20there%20was%20any%20shampoo.%20He%20laughed%2C%20telling%20me%20that%20my%20years%20abroad%20made%20me%20forget%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20survive%20in%20a%20war%20zone%3A%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%20we%20don't%20use%20shampoo!%20We%20are%20very%20lucky%20to%20have%20water%20to%20shower.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20here%20they%20didn't%20feel%20safe.%20The%20south%20was%20being%20hit%20by%20airstrikes%2C%20which%20the%20IDF%20claims%20are%20targeting%20militants.%20How%20could%20Israel%20order%20people%20to%20seek%20refuge%20in%20the%20south%20and%20then%20aim%20airstrikes%20at%20those%20that%20obeyed%3F%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20morning%2C%20Hanadi%20said%20she%20would%20return%20to%20her%20house%20in%20Gaza%20City%2C%20along%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20four%20children.%20If%20all%20of%20Gaza%20was%20under%20assault%2C%20at%20least%20she%20and%20the%20children%20should%20be%20comfortable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Despite%20the%20current%20circumstances'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20so%20difficult%20to%20keep%20track%20of%20everyone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20following%20the%20news%20minute%20by%20minute%2C%20so%20I%20know%20where%20the%20explosions%20are.%20If%20a%20neighborhood%20where%20my%20relatives%20are%20gets%20hit%2C%20I%20start%20calling%20them%20one%20by%20one.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20dial%20five%20numbers%20before%20someone%20picks%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20led%20us%20to%20create%20a%20single%20WhatsApp%20group%20for%20our%20whole%20family%20in%20Gaza.%20Every%20morning%2C%20or%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20have%20signal%2C%20my%20relatives%20type%20in%20their%20first%20initial%20to%20confirm%20they%20and%20their%20families%20are%20alive.%20If%20we%20have%20word%20from%20another%20relative%20who%20can't%20reach%20us%2C%20we%20share%20that%20too.%20As%20the%20day%20goes%20on%2C%20my%20relatives%20send%20selfies%2C%20or%20try%20to%20work%20out