tually%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20its%20way%20by%20dint%20of%20sheer%20numbers%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20should%20have%20been%20called%20ahead%20of%20the%20complainants%20according%20to%20several%20MPs%20who%20cited%20normal%20procedure%20to%20object%20to%20the%20latter%20being%20given%20time%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20opposition%20MP%2C%20eleven%20of%20the%2015%20MPs%20who%20are%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20formed%20by%20speaker%20Om%20Birla%20earlier%20this%20month%20were%20present%20in%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20chairman%20and%20BJP%20MP%20Vinok%20Kumar%20Sonkar%20called%20for%20a%20vote%20in%20which%20the%20BJP%20MPs%20fell%20in%20line.%20There%20was%20a%205-5%20split%20between%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20Opposition%20MPs%20and%20the%20chair%20got%20to%20cast%20the%20deciding%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20stumbling%20block%2C%20once%20the%20opposition%20was%20overruled%2C%20was%20when%20Moitra%20should%20be%20given%20time.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20chairman%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20call%20her%20on%20October%2031%20prevailed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20the%20five%20opposition%20MPs%20present%20in%20the%20meeting%20who%20told%20the%20chairman%20to%20call%20Moitra%20after%20November%2011%20because%20of%20the%20ongoing%20festivities%2C%E2%80%9D%20one%20MP%20present%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Five%20BJP%20MPs%20who%20were%20present%20there%20also%20initially%20said%20so.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20Sonkar%20was%20keen%20on%20summoning%20her%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%A6%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20Moitra%20has%20been%20called%20on%20October%2031%3B%20it%20is%20by%20dint%20of%20the%20numbers%20that%20the%20BJP%20had%20its%20way%20in%20the%20committee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20committee%20member%20told%20this%20correspondent%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20Opposition%20MPs%20questioned%20the%20chairman%20for%20calling%20the%20complainant%20first%20and%20not%20the%20accused.%20The%20House%20Ethics%20Committee%20is%20also%20ruled%20by%20the%20same%20directorate%20as%20the%20Privilege%20Committee%20which%20summons%20the%20accused%20first%20to%20depose%20before%20it.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20in%20the%20first%20meeting%20itself%2C%20before%20the%20members%20could%20first%20assemble%20to%20understand%20the%20complaint%2C%20the%20chairman%20called%20the%20complainants%2C%20Dubey%20and%20the%20lawyer%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20was%20odd%20was%20also%20that%20the%20chairman%20began%20the%20meeting%20by%20complimenting%20Dehadrai%20as%20a%20very%20senior%20lawyer%2C%20etc.%20Such%20cordiality%20between%20the%20complainants%20and%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee%20was%20striking.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20chairman%20also%20read%20out%20everything%20from%20a%20paper.%20Since%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20meeting%20were%20going%20as%20per%20that%20written%20paper%2C%20it%20seemed%20to%20me%20that%20the%20course%20of%20the%20meeting%20was%20pre-decided.%20When%20an%20Opposition%20MP%20was%20asking%20some%20questions%20to%20the%20chairman%2C%20he%20also%20read%20out%20from%20that%20paper%20to%20say%20to%20him%20that%20such%20questioning%20would%20not%20be%20acceptable%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20meeting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20cross-questioning%2C%20Dubey%20was%20pointedly%20asked%20about%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20that%20he%20had%20cited%20a%20fake%20MBA%20degree%20in%20his%20election%20nomination%20affidavit.%20The%20TMC%20MP%2C%20pointing%20it%20out%20to%20the%20Speaker%2C%20had%20asked%20recently%20if%20that%20is%20the%20case%2C%20should%20he%20not%20be%20disqualified%20from%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDubey%20didn%E2%80%99t%20clarify%20whether%20he%20had%20submitted%20a%20fake%20degree%20in%20his%20election%20nomination%20papers%20but%20only%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20didn%E2%80%99t%20entertain%20the%20allegation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDubey%20had%20claimed%20earlier%20that%20Dehradrai%20has%20documents%20to%20prove%20that%20Moitra%20took%20bribes%20from%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20to%20pose%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20While%20Dehadrai%20was%20asked%20by%20most%20MPs%20about%20it%2C%20all%20he%20could%20say%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20all%20mentioned%20in%20the%20affidavit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20opposition%20MP%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CDehradai%20spoke%20that%20line%20over%20a%20dozen%20times%20in%20the%20meeting.%20No%20documents%20were%20submitted%20as%20claimed%20by%20Dubey.%20It%20left%20us%20a%20bit%20confused%20because%20the%20affidavit%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20those%20details%20but%20Dehradai%20kept%20insisting%20it%20is%20all%20in%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20members%20also%20asked%20Dehadrai%20whether%20it%20was%20a%20personal%20fight%20with%20Moitra%20since%20it%20is%20all%20over%20social%20media%20that%20the%20real%20fight%20between%20the%20two%20was%20around%20a%20pet%20dog%20named%20Henry%20which%20Moitra%20refused%20to%20return%20to%20her%20%E2%80%98jilted%20ex%E2%80%99.%20If%20so%2C%20why%20should%20a%20parliamentary%20committee%20get%20into%20it%3F%20%E2%80%9CHe%20mumbled%20something%20but%20didn%E2%80%99t%20deny%20there%20was%20a%20fight%20over%20the%20dog%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20an%20MP%20present%20in%20the%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20Opposition%20MP%20also%20asked%20Dehadrai%20why%20he%20mentioned%20in%20the%20affidavit%20that%20he%20never%20met%20Dubey%20earlier%2C%20while%20a%20video%20shot%20some%20time%20ago%20and%20circulating%20on%20social%20media%20showed%20him%20interacting%20with%20Dubey%20at%20a%20social%20function.%20According%20to%20two%20MPs%2C%20in%20his%20defence%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BIt%20was%5D%20Not%20%5Ba%5D%20one-to-one%20meeting%20with%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20Opposition%20members%2C%20Preneet%20Kaur%20of%20Congress%2C%20Hemant%20Godse%20of%20Shiv%20Sena%20and%20B.%20Vallabbhaneni%20of%20YSR%20Congress%20were%20absent%20from%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoitra%20has%20outrightly%20denied%20Dubey%E2%80%99s%20allegations%2C%20while%20highlighting%20that%20it%20had%20come%20soon%20after%20she%20had%20questioned%20his%20%E2%80%98fake%20MBA%20degree%E2%80%99.%20The%20TMC%20MP%20has%20also%20been%20quite%20vocal%20in%20the%20Parliament%20and%20outside%20about%20Gautam%20Adani%2C%20the%20business%20tycoon%20seen%20close%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20More%20details%20on%20the%20complaint%20can%20be%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-modi-government-and-adani-train-guns-on-opposition-mp-mahua-moitra-heres-what-we-know-and-dont-know%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698334246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F03143050%2FDBTy8XrWAAAFLVI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fethics-committee-summons-mahua-moitra-on-oct-31-ignoring-mps-requests-to-delay-until-festival%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CThe%20chairman%20also%20read%20out%20everything%20from%20a%20paper.%20Since%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20meeting%20were%20going%20as%20per%20that%20written%20paper%2C%20it%20seemed%20to%20me%20that%20the%20course%20of%20the%20meeting%20was%20pre-decided%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20committee%20source%20told%20The%20Wire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fethics-committee-summons-mahua-moitra-on-oct-31-ignoring-mps-requests-to-delay-until-festival%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20100-Yo%20Heritage%20Fort%20in%20Kutch%20Is%20Home%20to%20a%20First-Of-Its-Kind%20CBSE%20School%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22