20Sameer%20Saxena%20and%20directors%20Biswapati%20Sarkar%20and%20Amit%20Golani%20didn%E2%80%99t%20come%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Netflix)%20during%20the%20lockdown%20imposed%20because%20of%20COVID-19.%20An%20uncertain%20time%20when%20many%20of%20us%20were%20sitting%20at%20home%2C%20watching%20films%20like%20Steven%20Soderbergh%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EContagion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2011)%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20assuming%20most%20filmmakers%20and%20writers%20saw%20possibilities%20for%20a%20pandemic%20thriller%2C%20especially%20with%20everything%20going%20on%20around%20us.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20one%20thing%20to%20brainstorm%20these%20ideas%2C%20and%20quite%20another%20to%20execute%20them.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20confidently%20mounted%2C%20and%20showcases%20an%20attribute%20that%20almost%20immediately%20makes%20one%20want%20to%20root%20for%20it%3A%20an%20ambitious%20scope%20of%20inquiry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESet%20in%20December%202027%20%E2%80%93%20as%20if%20to%20suggest%20a%20time%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20when%20human%20beings%20have%20forgotten%20about%20the%20horrors%20of%20COVID-19%20and%20have%20become%20predictably%20lax%20about%20social%20distancing%20%E2%80%93%20the%20show%20begins%20in%20Port%20Blair%20in%20the%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Islands.%20The%20show%E2%80%99s%20name%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20local%20name%20for%20the%20Cellular%20Jail%20in%20the%20capital%20city%20that%20was%20built%20by%20the%20British%20for%20the%20most%20%E2%80%98notorious%E2%80%99%20revolutionaries%2C%20chosen%20to%20serve%20particularly%20oppressive%20life%20sentences.%20The%20islands%20are%20pegged%20as%20a%20prison%2C%20surrounded%20by%20a%20wall%20no%20one%20could%20possibly%20scale%20%E2%80%93%20the%20endless%20sea.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6ph4WPZIrbM%3Fsi%3DOke9Eo4LjB7g0QmW%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20episode%20does%20well%20to%20introduce%20the%20main%20players%20of%20the%20show%20and%20set%20up%20the%20central%20conflict.%20Dr%20Soudamini%20Singh%20(Mona%20Singh%2C%20as%20assured%20as%20ever)%20has%20discovered%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20patients%20with%20black%20spots%20on%20the%20nape%20of%20their%20necks.%20All%20patients%20seem%20to%20exhibit%20similar%20symptoms%3A%20fever%20and%20hiccups%2C%20followed%20by%20death%20a%20few%20hours%20later.%20When%20Dr%20Singh%20brings%20this%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20her%20colleagues%2C%20they%20accuse%20her%20of%20being%20an%20alarmist.%20The%20island%20is%20going%20to%20be%20hosting%20a%20festival%20for%20tourists%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESwaraj%20Mahotsav%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(eerily%20sounds%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAzadi%20Ka%20Amrit%20Mahotsav%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20%E2%80%93%20and%20as%20one%20might%20be%20able%20to%20predict%20in%20such%20a%20show%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20outbreak%20on%20the%20island%20with%20the%20disease%20found%20to%20be%20spreading%20through%20a%20water%20pipeline%2C%20emerging%20from%20a%20lake.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuch%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EContagion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2011)%20%E2%80%93%20Soderbergh%E2%80%99s%20sharp%20and%20meticulous%20chronicling%20of%20an%20epidemic%2C%20right%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20H1N1%20breakout%20in%202009%20%E2%80%93%20even%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20characters%20come%20from%20all%20walks%20of%20life.%20This%20includes%20doctors%2C%20nurses%2C%20local%20administrators%2C%20politicians%2C%20cops%2C%20mainland%20tourists%2C%20local%20tour%20guides%2C%20ecological%20activists%2C%20and%20indigenous%20communities.%20It%20results%20in%20at%20least%20half%20a%20dozen%20subplots%2C%20covering%20the%20beats%20of%20a%20survival%20drama%20%E2%80%93%20a%20puppy%20romance%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20tracks%20around%20generational%20trauma%20being%20passed%20down%20%E2%80%93%20all%20this%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20main%20conflict%20of%20these%20characters%20getting%20through%20a%20widespread%20disease%20in%20the%20time%20of%20lockdown%2C%20where%20the%20administration%20is%20controlling%20the%20information%20to%20prevent%20public%20hysteria%20or%20simply%20to%20manipulate%20the%20public%20view%20of%20how%20is%20handling%20the%20crisis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20pleasure%20to%20see%20director%20Ashutosh%20Gowariker%20come%20back%20to%20acting%20after%20nearly%20two%20decades%2C%20as%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20(LG)%20Zibran%20Qadri%20%E2%80%93%20an%20admiral%20of%20the%20Indian%20Navy-turned-politician.%20As%20LG%20Qadri%2C%20Gowariker%20is%20precise%20%E2%80%93%20not%20giving%20his%20character%20unnecessary%20affectations%20and%20keeping%20it%20as%20uncluttered%20as%20possible%20%E2%80%93%20even%20though%20he%20seems%20conscious%20of%20the%20camera%20through%20a%20major%20chunk%20of%20his%20performance.%20Sukant%20Goel%2C%20as%20a%20slippery%20tour%20guide%20Chiranjeevi%2C%20is%20as%20potent%20as%20ever.%20His%20Tamil-inflected%20Hindi%20is%20consistent%2C%20and%20he%20gets%20one%20of%20the%20more%20interesting%20arcs%20in%20the%20show.%20Vikas%20Kumar%20%E2%80%93%20playing%20Santosh%20Savle%2C%20a%20working-class%20man%20from%20Bokaro%20visiting%20the%20island%20with%20his%20family%2C%20is%20another%20memorable%20character.%20Kumar%20has%20a%20disarming%20sincerity%20with%20the%20way%20he%20uses%20his%20big%20eyes%2C%20coarse%20body%20language%20and%20nothing-held-back%20approach%20during%20the%20big%20emotional%20scenes.%20Amey%20Wagh%20has%20fun%20playing%20Ketan%20Kamat%20%E2%80%93%20a%20corrupt%20cop%2C%20who%20acts%20as%20a%20liaison%20with%20the%20big%20corporate%20presence%20on%20the%20island%2C%20a%20company%20called%20Atom%20which%20wants%20to%20%E2%80%98develop%E2%80%99%20the%20islands%20by%20resettling%20the%20indigenous%20tribes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20well-acted%20for%20a%20large%20part.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20a%20few%20things%20stick%20out.%20Things%20that%20feel%20like%20writers%E2%80%99%20contrivance%20to%20take%20the%20show%20in%20a%20particular%20direction%2C%20rather%20than%20allowing%20it%20to%20take%20its%20own%20course.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20an%20early%20scene%20when%20a%20doctor%20argues%20with%20LG%20Qadri%20that%20the%20public%20should%20be%20informed%20about%20the%20disease%20amongst%20them%2C%20and%20therefore%20the%20need%20for%20social%20distancing%20and%20isolation%20%E2%80%93%20neither%20of%20them%20debates%20the%20panic%20that%20could%20be%20caused%20by%20the%20announcement.%20Qadri%20wants%20to%20control%20the%20information%20to%20his%20own%20advantage%2C%20while%20the%20doctor%20recklessly%20informs%20the%20media%20about%20the%20outbreak%2C%20without%20fully%20weighing%20the%20consequences%20of%20her%20actions.%20Similarly%2C%20Dr%20Soudamini%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20initiative%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20to%20track%20down%20her%20patients%2C%20putting%20herself%20in%20harm%E2%80%99s%20way%20for%20it%2C%20feels%20rushed%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20a%20cliffhanger%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20first%20episode.%20Several%20characters%20%E2%80%98coincidentally%E2%80%99%20identify%20patterns%20of%20a%20flower%20or%20a%20water%20bottle%20to%20make%20the%20tracks%20intersect%20during%20key%20moments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%2C%20there%20are%20too%20many%20tears.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20like%20most%20mainstream%20projects%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20serious%20problem%20with%20showing%20restraint%20and%20does%20not%20leave%20anything%20unsaid.%20Themes%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98man%20vs%20nature%E2%80%99%20conflict%20are%20verbalised%20through%20awkward%20lines%20like%20%E2%80%9Cnature%20always%20finds%20a%20way%E2%80%9D.%20The%20show%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20human%20nature%20is%20clunkily%20explained%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FThe_Scorpion_and_the_Frog%5C%22%3Efrog%20and%20scorpion%20fable%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20of%20the%20show%E2%80%99s%20core%20conflicts%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20one%20human%20life%20is%20more%20valuable%20than%20the%20other%2C%20and%20how%20one%20ascribes%20%E2%80%98value%E2%80%99%20to%20life%20is%20spoon-fed%20in%20the%20second%20episode%2C%20where%20LG%20Qadri%20explains%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merriam-webster.com%2Fwordplay%2Ftrolley-problem-moral-philosophy-ethics%5C%22%3Etrolley%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20with%20visual%20cues%20at%20a%20seminar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20certain%20kind%20of%20anxiety%20seems%20to%20underline%20these%20choices%20%E2%80%93%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20audience%20will%20not%20get%20it%E2%80%99%20unless%20it%E2%80%99s%20all%20spelt%20out.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20like%20the%20show%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20trust%20its%20merits%20enough%20to%20move%20the%20audience%20and%20thus%20injects%20decent%20scenes%20with%20exposition%20or%20melodrama.%20The%20show%2C%20which%20could%20have%20been%20leaner%2C%20also%20employs%20flashbacks%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20work.%20Like%20the%20corrupt%20cop%E2%80%99s%20telling%20of%20how%20he%20got%20his%20%E2%80%98punishment%20posting%E2%80%99%20in%20Andaman%2C%20or%20the%20trauma%20of%20a%20nurse%20played%20by%20Ayushi%20Sharma%2C%20which%20caused%20her%20to%20give%20up%20nursing.%20These%20flashbacks%20don%E2%80%99t%20add%20much%20to%20the%20characters%2C%20and%20are%20in%20retrospect%20wasteful%2C%20digressing%20from%20the%20show%E2%80%99s%20main%20narrative.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESameer%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20show%20could%20have%20been%20more%20adventurous%20with%20its%20treatment%20of%20indigenous%20tribal%20characters%20%E2%80%93%20who%20are%20sadly%2C%20even%20here%2C%20shown%20to%20be%20mute%2C%20noble%20spectators.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20much%20personality%2C%20apart%20from%20being%20respectful%20of%20nature%2C%20or%20being%20flogged%20by%20the%20city%20folk%20to%20show%20their%20%E2%80%98oppression%E2%80%99.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20one%20of%20the%20show%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20strengths%20is%20also%20that%20it%20stresses%20on%20the%20cruelty%20of%20%E2%80%98civilised%20society%E2%80%99.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20a%20few%20men%20in%20a%20room%20don%E2%80%99t%20hesitate%20even%20once%20while%20discussing%20the%20possibility%20that%20they%20may%20have%20to%20wipe%20out%20the%20entire%20indigenous%20tribe%20for%20their%20own%20survival.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20stunningly%20cruel%20moment%20delivered%20minus%20a%20dramatic%20background%20score%2C%20making%20it%20that%20much%20more%20chilling.%20Genocide%2C%20as%20an%20order%20of%20business%2C%20to%20be%20ticked%20off%20during%20a%20meeting%20among%20the%20powerful%20%E2%80%93%20one%20assumes%20this%20is%20how%20it%20happens%20across%20the%20world.%20There%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20superbly%20anti-climactic%20reveal%20about%20a%20secret%20project%20%E2%80%93%20designed%20in%20precisely%20that%20manner%20%E2%80%93%20to%20show%20capitalism%E2%80%99s%20reckless%20ways.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20track%20featuring%20Vikas%20Kumar%20is%20the%20only%20arc%20that%20feels%20like%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20allowed%20time%20to%20breathe.%20The%20climactic%20decision%2C%20and%20the%20horrific%20catharsis%20accompanying%20it%2C%20feel%20earned.%20The%20show%E2%80%99s%20commentary%20on%20%E2%80%98human%20desperation%E2%80%99%20isn%E2%80%99t%20underlined%2C%20making%20it%20all%20the%20more%20effective.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaala%20Paani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20competently%20made%20pandemic%20thriller%2C%20one%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20show%20enough%20faith%20in%20itself%20in%20key%20moments.%20Hopefully%2C%20there%20will%20be%20fewer%20tears%20in%20the%20second%20season.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698325836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26182128%2FScreenshot-2023-10-26-at-6.19.50%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkaala-paani-is-a-well-mounted-thriller-that-doesnt-trust-itself-enough-to-forgo-the-melodrama%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20acting%20is%20good%20across%20the%20board%20in%20this%20series%20about%20the%20outbreak%20of%20a%20strange%20disease%20in%20the%20near%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkaala-paani-is-a-well-mounted-thriller-that-doesnt-trust-itself-enough-to-forgo-the-melodrama%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Beating%20Odds%2C%20Security%20Guard%E2%80%99s%20Daughter%20Skates%20Her%20Way%20to%20National%20Gold%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAbove%20images%20courtesy%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fshredd_da%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShraddha%20Gaikwad%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHailing%20from%20Pune%E2%80%99s%20Wagholi%20town%2C%20Shraddha%20Gaikwad%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20rising%20star%20in%20the%20world%20of%20skateboarding.%20Recently%20clinching%20the%20gold%20at%20the%20National%20Games%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C