He%20is%20a%20cartoon%20character%20who%20was%20sketched%20to%20life%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20political%20cartoonist%2C%20Naji%20al-Ali%2C%20a%20towering%20presence%20across%20the%20Arab%20world%20for%20almost%20three%20decades%20until%20he%20was%20assassinated%2C%20in%20London%2C%20in%201987.%20It%20was%20through%20the%20figure%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwitness-child%E2%80%9D%20Handala%20in%20the%20cartoon%20frame%20that%20the%20uncompromisingly%20independent%20and%20sharp%20cartoonist%20unpacked%20his%20arsenal.%20Whether%20it%20be%20the%20story%20of%20the%20cruelty%20underlying%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20occupation%20of%20Palestine%2C%20the%20self-righteous%20and%20self-serving%20stance%20of%20western%20powers%2C%20the%20frequent%20vacillation%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20regimes%20on%20the%20Palestine%20question%2C%20or%20the%20pain%20of%20the%20common%20people%2C%20which%20was%20his%20pain%20as%20well%2C%20he%20was%20always%20there%20to%20bear%20witness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%2C%2036%20years%20after%20Naji%20al-Ali%E2%80%99s%20killing%2C%20the%20iconic%20Handala%20continues%20to%20symbolise%20the%20spirit%20of%20Palestinian%20resistance%2C%20it%20is%20because%20he%20%E2%80%98embodies%E2%80%99%20the%20experience%20of%20every%20dispossessed%20Palestinian%2C%20including%20the%20artist%2C%20in%20his%20very%20inception.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHandala%2C%20named%20after%20a%20local%20plant%20with%20deep%20roots%2C%20bitter%20fruit%20and%20a%20stubborn%20tendency%20to%20grow%20back%20when%20cut%2C%20is%20a%20barefoot%20urchin%20wearing%20frayed%20clothes.%20He%20reminds%20you%20of%20a%20child%20in%20a%20refugee%20camp.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20he%20stands%20with%20his%20back%20to%20the%20viewer%2C%20and%20his%20hands%20are%20clasped%20behind%20his%20back.%20The%20set%20of%20shoulders%20suggests%20a%20stance%20of%20digging%20in%2C%20not%20giving%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaji%20al-Ali%20visualised%20him%20as%20a%2010-year%20old.%20It%20was%20how%20old%20he%20was%20when%20he%20and%20his%20family%20were%20forced%20to%20flee%20Palestine%20during%20the%20%3Cem%3Enakba%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20catastrophe%20%E2%80%93%20of%201948%20that%20led%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20creation%2C%20turning%20more%20than%20750%2C000%20Palestinians%20into%20the%20dispossessed.%20The%20path%20away%20from%20home%20led%20them%20to%20the%20refugee%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26163820%2Fimage-1435.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22978%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26163820%2Fimage-1435.png%20978w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26163820%2Fimage-1435-300x206.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681873%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22672%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHandala%2C%20on%20a%20wall%20in%20Bilin%2C%20a%20Palestinian%20village.%20Photo%3A%20Public%20domain%2FWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fas-israel-kills-thousands-of-civilians-in-gaza-remember-the-international-community-helped-it-do-so%5C%22%3EAs%20Israel%20Kills%20Thousands%20of%20Civilians%20in%20Gaza%2C%20Remember%20the%20%E2%80%98International%20Community%E2%80%99%20Helped%20It%20Do%20So%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENaji%20al-Ali%E2%80%99s%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaji%20al-Ali%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Ayn%20al-Hilwa%20refugee%20camp%20in%20southern%20Lebanon.%20It%20was%20where%20the%20youngster%20experienced%20a%20political%20awakening%2C%20expressing%20political%20ideas%20through%20drawing%2C%20initially%20on%20prison%20walls%20and%20then%20on%20paper.%20His%20talent%20for%20drawing%20was%20first%20recognised%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20poet%20and%20journalist%20Ghassan%20Kanafani%2C%20launching%20him%20on%20a%20path%20that%20would%20draw%20the%20ire%20of%20the%20powerful%20and%20shower%20him%20with%20the%20love%20of%20common%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbout%20the%20birth%20of%20Handala%2C%20he%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20gave%20birth%20to%20this%20child%20in%20the%20Gulf%20and%20I%20presented%20him%20to%20the%20people.%20His%20name%20is%20Handala%20and%20he%20has%20promised%20the%20people%20that%20he%20will%20remain%20true%20to%20himself.%20I%20drew%20him%20as%20a%20child%20who%20is%20not%20beautiful%3B%20his%20hair%20is%20like%20a%20hedgehog%20who%20uses%20his%20thorns%20as%20a%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHandala%20is%20not%20a%20fat%2C%20happy%2C%20relaxed%2C%20or%20pampered%20child%2C%20he%20is%20barefooted%20like%20the%20refugee%20camp%20children%2C%20and%20he%20is%20an%20%E2%80%98icon%E2%80%99%20that%20protects%20me%20from%20making%20mistakes.%20Even%20though%20he%20is%20rough%2C%20he%20smells%20of%20amber.%20His%20hands%20are%20clasped%20behind%20his%20back%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20rejection%20at%20a%20time%20when%20solutions%20are%20presented%20to%20us%20the%20American%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHandala%20was%20born%20ten%20years%20old%2C%20and%20he%20will%20always%20be%20ten%20years%20old.%20At%20that%20age%20I%20left%20my%20homeland%2C%20and%20when%20he%20returns%2C%20Handala%20will%20still%20be%20ten%2C%20and%20then%20he%20will%20start%20growing%20up.%20The%20laws%20of%20nature%20do%20not%20apply%20to%20him.%20He%20is%20unique.%20Things%20will%20become%20normal%20again%20when%20the%20homeland%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20presented%20him%20to%20the%20poor%20and%20named%20him%20Handala%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20bitterness.%20At%20first%20he%20was%20a%20Palestinian%20child%2C%20but%20his%20consciousness%20developed%20to%20have%20a%20national%20and%20then%20a%20global%20and%20human%20perspective.%20He%20is%20a%20simple%20yet%20tough%20child%2C%20and%20this%20is%20why%20people%20adopted%20him%20and%20felt%20that%20he%20represents%20their%20consciousness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201984%2C%20during%20a%20conversation%20with%20Egyptian%20novelist%20and%20journalist%20Radwa%20Ashour%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.egypttoday.com%2FArticle%2F4%2F20561%2FNaji-Al-Ali-The-immortal-%5C%22%3E%2C%20he%20admitted%3A%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5B%E2%80%A6%5DThat%20child%20was%20like%20a%20splash%20of%20fresh%20water%20on%20my%20forehead%2C%20bringing%20me%20to%20attention%20and%20keeping%20me%20from%20error%20and%20loss.%20He%20was%20the%20arrow%20of%20the%20compass%2C%20pointing%20steadily%20to%20Palestine.%20Not%20just%20Palestine%20in%20geographical%20terms%2C%20Palestine%20in%20its%20humanitarian%20sense%20%E2%80%93%20the%20symbol%20of%20a%20just%20cause%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20located%20in%20Egypt%2C%20Vietnam%20or%20South%20Africa.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20to%20when%20Handala%E2%80%99s%20face%20would%20be%20visible%20to%20the%20world%2C%20the%20cartoonist%20and%20political%20activist%20had%20a%20simple%20answer%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20dignity%20is%20not%20threatened%20and%20when%20the%20Arabs%20regain%20their%20sense%20of%20freedom%20and%20humanity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrawing%20a%20Line%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20268px)%2085vw%2C%20268px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26163256%2FNaji_al_Ali_Graffiti_Ramallah_2012_AmerShomali-268x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22268%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26163256%2FNaji_al_Ali_Graffiti_Ramallah_2012_AmerShomali-268x300.jpg%20268w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26163256%2FNaji_al_Ali_Graffiti_Ramallah_2012_AmerShomali.jpg%20400w%5C%22%20class%3D