20villagers%20and%20locals%20were%20highly%20sceptical%20on%20whether%20such%20work%20could%20be%20done%20with%20community%20participation%20and%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20an%20NGO.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaking%20PPP%20work%3A%20Samast%20Mahajan%2C%20A.T.E.%20Chandra%20Foundation%20and%20more%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20those%20lamenting%20the%20failure%20of%20public%20and%20private%20partnerships%20in%20India%2C%20the%20water%20rejuvenation%20efforts%20of%20Maharashtra%20offers%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope.%20It%20was%20in%202013%20that%20Bain%20Capital%20chairman%20Amit%20Chandra%20%E2%80%94%20who%20set%20up%20and%20finances%20the%20A.T.E.%20Chandra%20foundation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Archana%2C%20started%20questioning%20why%20despite%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20and%20bluster%2C%20farmer%20suicides%20in%20the%20drought-hit%20state%20refused%20to%20abate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20rocket%20science%20to%20reach%20a%20quick%20answer-%20poor%20rainfall%20%3D%20failed%20crop%20season%20%3D%20farmer%20debt%20%3D%20farmer%20suicide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20they%20came%20across%20another%20NGO%20already%20working%20on%20the%20simple%20model%20they%20have%20since%20adopted-%20silt%20removal%20and%20rejuvenation%20of%20water%20bodies.%20Primary%20research%20done%20by%20them%20showed%20that%20there%20are%20many%20water%20bodies%20across%20the%20country%20that%20have%20over%20the%20years%20become%20defunct%20or%20unable%20to%20hold%20much%20water%20due%20to%20heavy%20silting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20groundwater%20too%20fails%20to%20get%20recharged%20as%20the%20silt%20prevents%20the%20rainwater%20from%20reaching%20the%20bottom.%20But%20if%20someone%20removed%20the%20silt%2C%20the%20water%20body%20could%20be%20rejuvenated%20and%20even%20better%20the%20silt%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20usually%20quite%20fertile%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20used%20by%20farmers%20on%20their%20land%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F268059%2Fmeena-pawar-nashik-farmer-earns-lakhs-grape-debt-farming-success-story-inspiring%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimprove%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%202016%20to%202019%2C%20the%20A.T.E%20CF%2C%20along%20with%2022-odd%20partner%20organisations%2C%20worked%20extensively%20in%20Maharashtra%20to%20rejuvenate%20over%202%2C700%20water%20bodies%2C%20impacting%20around%204%2C200%20villages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20dampened%20their%20efforts%20but%20did%20not%20stop.%20In%202020%20and%202021%2C%20work%20continued%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Karnataka.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20work%20picked%20up%20pace%20once%20again%20and%20916%20water%20bodies%20were%20rejuvenated%20in%2018%20districts%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20some%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Niti%20Aayog%20which%20had%2C%20by%20then%2C%20pulled%20in%20by%20the%20foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20768px)%20100vw%2C%20768px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%20India%20is%20placed%20at%20120th%20amongst%20122%20countries%20in%20the%20water%20quality%20index%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20water%20being%20contaminated.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718-500x375.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718-150x113.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332697%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%20India%20is%20placed%20at%20120%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20amongst%20122%20countries%20in%20the%20water%20quality%20index%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20water%20being%20contaminated.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENiti%20Aayog%20buys%20in%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%202021-22%20that%20the%20A.T.E%20CF%20team%20decided%20to%20approach%20Niti%20Aayog%20which%20quickly%20bought%20into%20the%20scheme.%20In%20June%202018%2C%20Niti%20Aayog%20had%20brought%20out%20a%20report%20on%20%E2%80%9CComposite%20Water%20Management%20Index%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20mentions%20that%20India%20is%20undergoing%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F262905%2Fmaharashtra-girl-cycles-drought-prone-farmer-water-conservation-pranali-chikte%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworst%20water%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20history%20and%20that%20nearly%20600%20million%20people%20are%20facing%20high%20to%20extreme%20water%20stress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20further%20mentions%20that%20India%20is%20placed%20at%20120%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20amongst%20122%20countries%20in%20the%20water%20quality%20index%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20water%20being%20contaminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20model%20presented%20by%20the%20foundation%20to%20the%20Niti%20Aayog%20could%20be%20scaled%20very%20quickly%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost%20to%20unleash%20water%20security%20in%20drought%20prone%20regions.%20It%20was%20community-led%20with%20farmers%20bearing%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20cost%20and%20aligns%20almost%20perfectly%20with%20the%20Amrit%20Sarovar%20mission%20launched%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20in%20April%202022%20where%20the%20plan%20is%20to%20rejuvenate%20and%20develop%2075%20water%20bodies%20in%20each%20and%20every%20district%20of%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20approach%20of%20building%20new%20water%20bodies%2C%20dams%20and%20canals%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20ecologically%20and%20environmentally%20damaging%20and%20often%20leads%20to%20large%20scale%20displacement%20of%20the%20locals%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20500%20water%20bodies%20were%20rejuvenated%20with%20financial%20support%20from%20NITI%20Aayog.%20Currently%2C%20pilot%20projects%20are%20ongoing%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20MP%2C%20Rajasthan%20and%20Maharashtra%2C%20with%20a%20view%20to%20extending%20this%20to%20all%20its%20aspirational%20districts%20and%20regions%20that%20are%20water%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20614px)%20100vw%2C%20614px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20senior%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20official%20says%20that%20drought%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20nemesis%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%20since%20he%20has%20been%20posted%20and%20based%20there.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253.jpeg%20614w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253-500x281.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.23-1_11zon-1697802253-150x84.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332699%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20senior%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20official%20says%20that%20drought%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20nemesis%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%20since%20he%20has%20been%20posted%20and%20based%20there.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaharashtra%20goes%20all%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%2050%20years%2C%20droughts%20and%20floods%20in%20Maharashtra%20have%20risen%20sevenfold%20and%20sixfold%20respectively.%20It%20was%20after%20the%20latest%20devastating%20droughts%20faced%20by%20the%20state%20in%202013-2016%20that%20the%20state%20intensified%20its%20efforts%20on%20making%20defunct%20water%20bodies%20functional.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20official%20says%20that%20drought%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20nemesis%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%20since%20he%20has%20been%20posted%20and%20based%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20rejuvenated%20over%205%2C000%20water%20bodies%20across%20the%20state%20between%202017-2019%2C%20mostly%20through%20the%20GDGS%20(Gaalmukt%20Dharan%2C%20Gaalmukt%20Shivar)%20Scheme.%20At%20this%20time%2C%20donors%20were%20providing%20the%20rental%20charges%20for%20the%20machines%20for%20silt%20removal%2C%20the%20state%20paid%20for%20the%20diesel%20and%20the%20farmers%20for%20the%20carting%20of%20silt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20recently%2C%20faced%20with%20the%20threat%20of%20El%20Nino%20and%20erratic%20rain%20patterns%2C%20the%20state%20decided%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20wait%20for%20donors%20or%20other%20philanthropic%20funding%20and%20that%20it%20would%20fund%20the%20full%20effort%20on%20its%20own%20steam%20for%20now.%C2